Rg5+ would be so much cooler if that stupid pawn at c5 wasn't there. Took me a while to find a move I liked here. b3 seemed like the best move to hold onto that pawn. I didn't see any benefit in letting his Q onto the 7th rank.

I think the h6 was out of habit, maybe? I don't have my bishop in position for a pin, but it blocks it if I decided to do it later on g5. I'm just not a huge fan of a6 or h6 anymore. Moving my Q out to threaten his with a bishop in a move or two and then I could force a trade with Bcxf6 and make him start stacking pawns.
